Package: log4j
Version: 1.1.3
Revision: 1
BuildDepends: ant
Depends: junit, xerces-j
Source: http://jakarta.apache.org/log4j/jakarta-%n-%v.tar.gz
PatchScript: <<
sed 's:@FINK_PREFIX@:%p:g' <"%a/%f.patch" | patch -p1
rm -r build/lib
<<
CompileScript: chmod 755 build.sh ; ./build.sh jar javadoc
InstallScript: <<
mkdir -p %i/share/java/%n
cp dist/lib/*.jar %i/share/java/%n

mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
cp -r docs/* %i/share/doc/%n

mkdir -p %i/etc/profile.d
install -m 755 %n.sh %i/etc/profile.d/
install -m 755 %n.csh %i/etc/profile.d/
<<
DocFiles: INSTALL LICENSE.APL
Description: Tool for Java programmers to generate data logs
DescDetail: <<
In case of problems with an application, it is helpful to enable logging so that the problem can be located. With log4j it is possible to enable logging at runtime without modifying the application binary.
<<
DescPort: profile.d scripts to add the jars to the CLASSPATH
DescPackaging: <<
	- cp the docs to share/doc/%n
	- cp the jars to share/java/%n
remove build/lib to make sure to not use those jars but fink's one (xerces-j)
depends junit to enable test code
<<
